        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your note just to hand. I am sorry you think of<lb/> coming by so late a train&#44; for you may need a little rest before hurrying<lb/> to Synagogue. As to your going away same night that will be too much<lb/> fatigue&#59; I shall therefore meet you Sunday and look after your &#34;creature&#45;<lb/> comforts&#34;¬ù personally. You are the guest of our congregation and I hope will<lb/> stay at least over night. Moreover I want to have a good talk with you and<lb/> Papa upon matters&#44; and nothing but good to our cause can come of it&#44; for<lb/> we can discuss certain matters and both of you can advise me as to the<lb/> handling of the new orthodox movement in which I have designedly kept<lb/> my finger in order to shape it as much as possible when the time<lb/> comes. I have invited the President or Secretary of the Association to meet<lb/> me at synagogue Sunday aft&#39;noon at service. Please send me a<lb/> <sic>despatch</sic> &#40;night&#45;message&#41; tomorrow night saying when you are <del>fin</del> due<lb/> in New York and by what railroad you come. Good Shabat. Yrs H P Mendes<lb/></p>
                
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North 5th<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
